commit_message: Updated installation script
Updated statistics reporting
Began writing function to report descriptive statistics about the distribution of binding data for each set of genes at each relative genomic region.
Continuted updating functions for statistical testing. Removed unreasonable tests.
Completed Wilcoxon Rank Sum Test functions. Still need to do a bit more testing.
Wrote example script to calculate Wilcoxon Rank Sum two-tailed p-value using normal approximation.
Adding functions to calculate Fisher exact test and the exact p-value for the Wilcoxon Rank Sum test.
Finished writing functions to separate binding by gene lists. Began reworking statistical testing functions into attributes.

Fixed huge bugs in enrichment ratio calculation. Ratios are now scaled by genomic window size. Further, ratios are averaged over the sum of lengths of introns and exons. Began working on functions to rapidly extract binding data from the PtG database for statistical testing.
Making major changes to PeaksToGenes::SignalRatio. At the point where the database insertion function needs to be written.
Wrote function to dynamically determine window size based on gene size
Merge branch 'performance'
Finished the addition of Wilcoxon. Added function to calculate SEM
Created install script. Fixed scaling bug.
Updated installation instructions and added script for easier installation
Added GPL to top of all files
Added checking for external executables for the peaksToGenes.pl script
Began removing kruskal-wallis functions
Began adding Wilcoxon Rank-Sum test and p-value approximation functions
Fixed dying when making a matrix and accession entered is not found in RefSeq database.
Fixed matrix function to reflect 10Kb limit.
Updated contrast functions to reflect the 10Kb limits and the use of only peak numbers.
When invalid accessions are found in the user-defined genome, they are printed for the user.
Added SQL protection against multiple transcript IDs per genome.
Modified the update function to only create genomic indexes to 10Kb. Added a .gitignore file to the static directory to ensure that this directory would be included when cloning the repository.
Trimmed database to only include 10Kb from TSS and TES. Removed annotation tables (derived from peak scores) as well.
Added zlib dependency warning.
Require BedTools source version.
Updated MySQL installation for Ubuntu.
Updated Ubuntu line for MySQL installation.
Began preparing for release by updating install files.
Removed testing stop.
Added functions to export a matrix file for clustering or making a heat map. Also updated the signal ratio function to run slightly faster.
Merge branch 'fasterextraction' into develop
Increased the speed of the fetching algorithm by inflating the DBIx::Class::ResultSets into Hash Refs.
Added a test for ANOVA reporting.
Edited so that the p-value would be correctly evaulated.
Modified BedTools so that it will recognize genomic coordiantes correctly.
Fixed list behavior.
Merge branch 'statistics' into develop
Finished adding statistical functions and annotating BED-format reads.
Added PeaksToGenes::Contrast::Out to print the tables to file.
Added PeaksToGenes::Contrast::Aggregate, which does basic aggregation and mean determinate functions.
Added PeaksToGenes::Contrast::ParseStats to parse the output from the statistical tests into tables for printing.
Kept old string method of reporting. Can't figure out API.
Added the Fisher-like test for ANOVA one-way parametric testing as well as a test harness
Testing parallel functions
Further testing of parallelization
Edited function
Updated threading
Fixed Array Ref of Array Ref error in the parsing of peak annotations
The annotation functions have multi-threaded functionality added to them. Updating a genome takes approximately 30 seconds
Added threading functionality to the parsing and creation of the insert statment in PeaksToGenes::Annotate::Database
Added threaded functionality to PeaksToGenes::Annotate::BedTools
Added point biserial corraltion function and test harness
Updated threading functions
Updated algorithm to make sure the background list of genes is unique. Added threading to the fetching of information from the tables.
Moved the Wilcoxon test to t/11-wilcoxon
Added a subroutine to PeaksToGenes::Contrast::Genes to ensure that the user-defined list of background genes will be unique from the test list of genes
Added Wilcoxon testing in the form of a two group Kruskal-Wallis test with normalization for duplicate values. Need to find a better test dataset for t/11-wilcoxon.t, preferably one with less zeros.
Merge branch 'offline' into statistics
Added the PeaksToGenes::Annotate::BedTools::chromosome_sizes subroutine to fetch the chromosome sizes from the user-defined genome using local files defined by the PeaksToGenes::Update module.
Added functions and complimentary tests so that the chromosome sizes file will be stored in the PeaksToGenes database and can be referenced by the genome_id in the AvailableGenome table.
Fixed SQL and DBIx definitions for the chromosome sizes table.

Modified db/peakstogenes.sql so that a table for the chromosome sizes has been added. Used dbicdump to update the PeaksToGenes::Schema and the result sets PeaksToGenes::Schema::Result::AvailableGenome and PeaksToGenes::Schema::Result::ChromosomeSize. Added a method in PeaksToGenes::Update::UCSC to write the chromosome sizes to file and return to PeaksToGenes::Update both the Array Ref of file strings for the index files, as well as the file string for the chromosome sizes file. Concomitantly, I added a test harness for these functions to t/02-update_ucsc.t.
Added files to statistics branch
Saved status to move development to HPCC
Cleaned up PeaksToGenes::Contrast::GenomicRegions and will begin work on PeaksToGenes::Contrast::Stats
Initial commit of development branch
PeaksToGenes::Contrast::GenomicRegions now fetches arrays of peak numbers per kb and peak scores

Began work on the PeaksToGenes::Contrast::GenomicRegions module along with t/09-genomicregions.t the complimentary test script to test the functions of the PeaksToGenes::Contrast::GenomicRegions module. This module is designed to fetch the peaks information for a user-defined subset of genes from a previously annotated set of peaks.

Began work on refactoring the contrast testing algorithm. Wrote a module to handle extraction of transcript IDs from the database based on the user-defined files for a test list. At the same time, this module can either extract a list of background IDs from a user-defined file, or a list of background IDs using the rest of the transcripts in the user-defined genome. Wrote a test harness t/08-genes.t to test these functions. Added example data taken from Carroll et al 2006 to the test directory.
Refactored the annotate function
Added a test harness for PeaksToGenes::Annotate
Added a test harness for PeaksToGenes::Annotate::Database
Added a test harness for PeaksToGenes::Annotate::BedTools
Added a test harness for PeaksToGenes::Annotate::FileStructure
Refactored the annotation program structure to be more similar to a MVC-type program.
Using test script 04-annotate.t, I  have learned the points at which the script was being slowed. I have optimized the algorithm to run approximately 20x faster than the previous implementation.
Moved database functions from PeaksToGenes::Out to PeaksToGenes::Database. When completed, PeaksToGenes::Out will only have functions that print tables to file
Modified deciles algorithm to correctly calculate deciles for genes on the negative strand

Modified PeaksToGenes::BedTools so that it will no longer create an index of every genes, instead it will only create an index of genes whose genomic regions intersect with the user-defined peaks. This dramatically increases the time it takes for database storage.
Normalized database to separate into smaller relational tables to increase speed for inserts. Updated DBIx transaction code to match new structure.
Update intersection function call to BedTools to use the -wo instead of -wb call
Updated peak coordinate and score reporting
Updated capitalization of gene body column names
Updated interval measurement and testing
Fixed coordinate assignment for gene body decile positioning for the tenth decile
Refactored PeaksToGenes::BedTools and added a test harness includedin t/04-annotate.
Refactored PeaksToGenes::FileStructure and added a test harness for the functions in PeaksToGenes::FileStructure
Added a function to test for the existence and executability of MySQL

Added a test harness for the PeaksToGenes::Update module and updated the SQLite code for the addition of the gene body deciles. Added a test harness to ensure that BedTools and SQLite3 are installed in the users $PATH
Added a test module to test the required external dependencies of PeaksToGenes
Added database functions for separating gene bodies into deciles
Refactored PeaksToGenes::Update::UCSC. Added a test script (t/02-update_ucsc.t) to test the functions of PeaksToGenes::Update::UCSC.
Updated aggregate peak functionality to determine the relative number of peaks per Kb. Increased number of relative locations to 100 for both upstream and downstream.

Added dynamic database creation
